The South African National Taxi Council has spoken to Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula over their planned fare increase. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Transport MEC Jacob Mamabolo says there won't be a taxi fare increase on 15 June, despite an announcement by taxi associations. Taxi drivers have raised concerns about the fuel price increase and the impact that the lockdown has had on their ability to pay vehicle finance instalments. Mamabolo says he's noted the challenges and will follow up on the taxi industry's demands for access to government relief. READ: Commuters hit with taxi fare increase "Come the 15th of June, there shouldn't be any taxi association in our province that will increase the fares," said Mamabolo. He has urged the transport sector to be mindful of the plight of the poor.